message.content: Hello — I'm just a virtual assistant, so I don't have feelings, but I'm ready and able to help. What can I do for you today?

I don’t have live data access, so I can’t tell you the current conditions. I can:

- Give a quick summary of San Francisco’s typical weather, or
- Tell you how to check current conditions and a forecast right now (websites, phone commands, or a one-line terminal command), or
- If you share a date/time (or your ZIP), I can give a typical expected range for that time of year.

Quick summary of typical weather in San Francisco
- Climate: cool Mediterranean with strong microclimates. Summer is often cool and foggy (esp. mornings/evenings) — “June–September gloom.” Winters are mild and wetter.
- Typical ranges:
  - Summer (Jun–Sep): highs about 60–68°F (16–20°C), lows 50–56°F (10–13°C).
  - Fall (Oct–Nov): highs 61–70°F (16–21°C), lows 50–55°F (10–13°C).
  - Winter (Dec–Feb): highs 55–62°F (13–17°C), lows 45–52°F (7–11°C); rainy periods.
  - Spring (Mar–May): highs 58–66°F (14–19°C), lows 46–54°F (8–12°C).
- Note: Conditions can vary a few miles — the coast and Golden Gate area are much cooler and foggier than the Mission or Daly City.

How to get the current weather right now
- Phone: Ask Siri/Google Assistant/Alexa “What’s the weather in San Francisco?”
- Web: National Weather Service (https://www.weather.gov/sfo), Weather.com, AccuWeather, or OpenWeatherMap.
- Quick terminal/browser line: open https://wttr.in/San%20Francisco or run
  curl "https://wttr.in/San%20Francisco?format=3"
  (returns a one-line current-condition summary).

Do you want me to give the forecast for a specific day or show those quick commands/links?
